metadata.name: Winter Sun on Watercolour #9
metadata.description:
Slightly-transparent white is slathered generously on a gray canvas. Triangles are created using a Gaussian-distributed random number sequence, causing the center to whiten.

Triangles of three hash-influenced hues are spread liberally to form a gentle, triple-rainbow of colour, upon which a milky, misted winter sun is placed.

Ad meliora; ad oculos; beatae memoriae!

metadata.name: Avoidance #172
metadata.description: Created with Javascript and p5js. Each bar steers clear of the other bars and balls. This is an experiment in which I admittedly invested a little too much time. The numerous variables, factors, and variants ensure that each mint has a distinct outcome.

metadata.name: Sea of Shapes #127
metadata.description:
This program was inspired by the 2022 Genuary prompt "Make a sea of shapes." It is an abstract and geometric representation of water and waves. I tried to capture the many different possible states of a sea (windy, breezy, calm etc.) by changing parameters within the program for different outputs.

Press 'p' while on Live View to save a high quality (4000x4000) png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js

metadata.name: Windswept #119
metadata.description:
Windswept

Press 's' in live view to download a copy of your image.

You can add the URL parameter 'scale' to scale the size of the image for a higher resolution download (1600x2000 by default). For example, for a 3200x4000 image, add '&scale=2' to the end of the URL. 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 are valid inputs. (Warning: large numbers may not work depending on your hardware/browser and can produce a very large download file of ~100mb)

metadata.name: Ornithic #201
metadata.description:
Pure p5.js code. No svg, no image, no other materials. Creating code arts with polar coordinate system and algorithms are my passion. This generative art contains a lot of features that may be rare than common.  

• 30 color palettes // 2 of them have 3 different colors
• 4 grass structures // With the same algorithm 
• 16 flower types //  Count, leaf number and size
• 6 color functions // Different colorizations with b&w 

Also, the outputs of the project are very high resolution to print or something like that.
April / 2022
Rhaegar

metadata.name: Ganymede at Sunset II #20
metadata.description:
Note:
This token is CPU intensive and may take a while to render. Thank you for your patience.


Description:
Ganymede at Sunset is a series inspired by the swirling, nebulous forms generated by fluid pouring techniques.
It features sketches in :

- 12 unique color palettes
- 10% rarity gets an inverted background


How to get more variants:
Click on the sketch to generate a variant with a different color palette.


How to save the sketch:
To save a JPG file, press 's' on your keyboard.


Made by Sudev Kiyada (@Generalissimo) with p5.js

metadata.name: The Ocean Waves #6
metadata.description:
Ocean waves in calm or stormy skies. Spray, and the occasional buoy passes by.

Large and rolling waves are generated at the back and get more turbulent as they get closer to the viewer. A stripe of sunlight varies in position from towards the back to the front. The highest waves create spray. Everyone once and a while, a buoy or two (or more!) will pass by. The background color is related to the buoy color to make it more harmonious.

metadata.name: Top of Mountains #29
metadata.description:
Isn't the view beautiful on top of the mountains?

Sky, clouds, and mountains are generated with random dots, lines and shapes.
Made with p5.js.

Features:
1. Time: Day/Sunset/Night
2. Clouds: Yes/None
3. Light Source: Left/Right

Keys:
s: save the image as PNG
2: save the image in medium resolution 2000x2000
4: save the image in high resolution 4000x4000

When saving the image in medium/high resolutions, please note that it takes several seconds to redraw before the image is downloaded.

metadata.name: Fronteras en abstracto #106
metadata.description:
A place in the abstract, walking in one direction without knowing if you will reach that place. Then, in case you find it, go to the other side before dawn.

It's just a game of words and phrases that have to be given meaning, and we find it on the frontier of something that we don't know what it is.

//

Un lugar en abstracto, caminando en una dirección sin saber si se llega a ese lugar. Luego, en caso de encontrarlo, pasar al otro lado antes del amanecer.

Es solo un juego de palabras y frases a las cuales hay que darles sentido, y lo encontramos en la frontera de algo que no sabemos qué es.

//


Keys

[s] -> download still image (in live view)
[1,2,3,4] Pixel ratios
